When investigators looked more closely, they found that the boys’ medical exemptions had been written by a doctor hundreds of miles away from their home.
Currently, schools are charged with deciding whether to accept medical exemptions written by doctors.
“So, now families have to go back every three months and pay $300 to get their temporary medical exemption updated.
Currently, West Virginia and Mississippi are the only two states that require medical exemptions to be cleared by a central authority.
“Every time a child receives a false medical exemption, when a physician has forgotten their oath, they are putting other children at risk.”